data.description: Get ready to Fall in love with your charming, 1925 Bungalow in Bartow. This tastefully updated 3-bedroom, 1-bathroom home is located in the heart of Historical Bartow. Truly charming, as it's situated on a peaceful street in the downtown district. Entering, you will be greeted with extensive original hardwood floors that lead to a wide-open living area. Cozy up on chilly evenings by the wood-burning fireplace accented with original brick. The kitchen has been beautifully updated with granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, and custom cabinetry. The detail and love that was invested in the fine craftsmanship throughout the entire home would impress even the most experienced and seasoned carpenter.   The master bedroom is spacious and includes an attached 3rd bedroom, with a large closet, perfect for a nursery. Storage space is ample throughout as the additional bedrooms and hallways have closet space to spare. Double-pane windows and plantation shutters provide plenty of natural light and period correct style throughout the home with modern convenience.  Outside, you'll find a huge 700 sq ft detached garage/workshop with electric, water and two bay doors, perfect for all your projects or storage needs. The front porch area is ready for a new rocking chair to ease your stress away. Backyard BBQs or fireside gatherings will be a hit this summer with all your oved ones. Highlighted features include a newer roof, AC, and water heater. With no HOA, your new home offers plenty of freedom and space for your lifestyle.   Conveniently located near shopping, restaurants, medical facilities, Bartow Golf Course, and major highways (Hwy 98 and Hwy 60), you'll have easy access to all that Florida has to offer. Don't miss out on this opportunity to own a piece of history with modern amenities and conveniences. Call today for your private showing!
